    <title>IADLXLog</title>
    <innerpage refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_log__write_log">WriteLog</innerpage>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <bold>IADLXLog</bold> interface is implemented in the application to receive the log traces from the internal code execution of ADLX.</para>
<para><table rows="4" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>InterfaceId:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Smart Pointer Interface Name:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherits:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherited By:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para>If the application wants the ADLX log traces to be integrated in the application&apos;s own log system, an instance of the implemented <bold>IADLXLog</bold> interface must be passed to <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_system__enable_log" kindref="compound">EnableLog</ref> along with <bold>APPLICATION</bold> in the <ref refid="group__enumerations_1gae308b7ad24806dce3fe087e9a780be67" kindref="member">ADLX_LOG_DESTINATION</ref> parameter.<linebreak/>
 The log instance must exist until ADLX is terminated.</para>
<para><heading level="2">Methods </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Method   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_log__write_log" kindref="compound">WriteLog</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>The <bold>WriteLog</bold> method is called by ADLX when a new ADLX log message is available.   </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Requirements </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Header</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>include &quot;ISystem.h&quot;</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Minimum version</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>1.0</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Example </heading>
</para>
<para>To see how to use this interface in a C++ application, refer to the <ref refid="cpp_sample_log" kindref="compound">Log C++ sample</ref>.<linebreak/>
 For a C application, refer to the <ref refid="c_sample_log" kindref="compound">Log C sample</ref>.</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_log__write_log" kindref="compound">WriteLog</ref> </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
